findings.recommendation:
Wrap the `extractBigModelErrorCode` extraction in a guard: `if (!response.ok)`. This ensures that vendor application-level error parsing only occurs when the HTTP status indicates a failure. For example:

javascript
if (!response.ok) {
  const vendorCode = extractBigModelErrorCode(responseText);
  if (vendorCode) {
    const vendor = classifyBigModelError(vendorCode, responseText, { endpoint, model });
    return failureShape(vendor.message, vendor.errorCode, {
      rawResponse: responseText,
      vendorCode: vendor.vendorCode,
      vendorMessage: vendor.vendorMessage,
      retry: vendor.retry
    });
  }
}

